feat(dossiers+variants): quality pass — sharper selection, R3F dossier, signaturePatterns, embedding-driven variant pick

DOSSIER SELECTION (M2 + M3)
- Raised EMBEDDING_MIN_SCORE 0.2 → 0.3 in src/lib/gen/dossiers/select.ts
  to drop weak matches (Weaviate at ~0.22 was spilling into SaaS prompts).
- Lowered DEFAULT_MAX_TOTAL 6 → 5 for tighter prompt focus.
- Rewrote payments-stripe-checkout summary to lead with subscription/
  monthly billing/recurring/SaaS/abonnemang so embedding matching
  prioritises Stripe over Paddle for SaaS prompts. Added matching tags.

  Smoke-select result for "SaaS med användarinloggning, månadsabonnemang":
    before: paddle 0.506, no stripe in top 4
    after:  stripe 0.673, weaviate gone

NEW DOSSIER: ai-3d-scene-r3f (K3 + K4 mitigation)
- Hand-curated dossier with verified peer-dep pins (three@^0.170 +
  @react-three/fiber@^9 + @react-three/drei@^10) — fixes the v1 SaaS
  generation that produced incompatible R3F deps.
- Self-containment rule front and centre: every imported mesh component
  MUST also be generated, never imported "from the air".
- floating-scene.tsx + floating-mesh.tsx as concrete starting code so the
  runtime LLM sees both files when importing one references the other.

SCAFFOLD VARIANTS — signaturePatterns replaces removed guidance fields
- Added optional signaturePatterns { layouts, motifs, antiPatterns } to
  ScaffoldVariant type + JSON schema. Replaces the four generic fields
  (styleRules, sectionInventory, avoidPatterns, worldClassRubric)
  removed in commit fd0f326df — those produced boilerplate.
- New script scripts/scaffolds/auto-curate-variant-patterns.ts: GPT-5.4
  reads each variant + sourceTemplateIds and produces strict, CONCRETE
  patterns via Zod (layouts must read like "60/40 hero with floating
  product card" not "modern layout"; motifs like "1rem radii + soft
  shadow" not "subtle design"; antiPatterns honest to the variant).
- Ran against all 21 variants — 21/21 curated, no failures, ~3 min total.
- system-prompt.ts now renders three new lists in the Scaffold Variant
  block: Signature layouts / Signature motifs / Avoid for this variant.
- variant-hints.ts forwards top-3 layouts + top-2 motifs to the Brief-LLM
  pre-match.
- generate-variant-embeddings.ts includes signaturePatterns text in the
  embedding source so semantic match becomes more accurate. Re-ran for
  all 21 variants.

VARIANT MATCHING — embedding-driven by default (was dead code)
- pickScaffoldVariantAsync was built in pass 8 (commit 507031171) but
  never wired in production. orchestrate.ts now uses it:
  resolveScaffoldVariant is async and calls pickScaffoldVariantAsync
  which falls back to keyword pickScaffoldVariant when embeddings or
  OPENAI_API_KEY missing.
- Stream pre-match call sites (create-chat-stream-post, chat-message-
  stream-post) intentionally KEEP keyword pickScaffoldVariant — they
  feed Brief-LLM hints in <1ms; +500ms embedding round-trip there is
  wasted because final pick happens later in orchestrate.
- system-prompt.ts buildDynamicContext keeps keyword fallback for the
  rare path where resolvedVariant isn't pre-supplied (legacy tests,
  snapshot rendering) so the function stays sync.

DOCS + CONFIG
- docs/architecture/scaffold-schema.md: new rows 22 (signaturePatterns)
  + 23 (embedding-driven variant pick).
- docs/schemas/strict/scaffold-variant.schema.json: signaturePatterns
  required-when-present validation.
- package.json: scaffolds:variant-patterns + :dry npm scripts.
- egna_kommandon.txt previously updated.
- .gitignore: logs/variant-patterns-batch.log.

VERIFICATION
- npx tsc --noEmit clean.
- vitest run src/lib/gen/dossiers/ src/lib/gen/scaffold-variants/ → 13/13 green.
- smoke-select.ts: pool=23 (was 22), Stripe wins all subscription queries,
  Weaviate no longer spills.

